<br>
Egads, it is true that there is little roleplay and the roleplay that does exist usually revolves around the use of simple commands (Soandso bows before whatshisname) or cybering. (Not that there is anything bad with that but it always seems like the silly romances and sexual innuendo are the order of the day).<br>
<br>
Now during the few months that I played I have seen roleplay however, some good roleplay too, but it was always of a very sporadic and momentary nature. What Firiona Vie misses I suppose are people with intentions to create long lasting storylines and character interactions, be they based on love, fear anger or hate. <br>
<br>
I myself play a stoic, prideful human warrior who is single-minded in his quest for vengeance against the Tier'dal who sacked his family's estate and killed much of his kinsmen. Whenever I act even suspicious or somewhat aloof against the dark elves however I already get booted from groups and yelled at, so you can imagine how difficult it is for my quest to find a personification for my nemesis.<br>
<br>
Again roleplay could work, if there were some long lasting storylines people could be made aware of, I think guilds could play a good role in that.<br>
<br>
Until such time there will be much ranting and muttering from this here warrior, until he finds a good enough Tier'dal for some (verbal) fencing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=feneant>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 954<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/13/04 4:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=363.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lack of extremes</span><hr size=1> There is not much true roleplay anymore I find, it's mostly in the form of events, no ooc or other things like this, nothing hard core where it's only roleplay.  It's hard to roleplay as well as its a word, its all in the way you act and behave and so my idea of roleplay might be different than yours or whatever.<br>
<br>
When the server began, it was mostly roleplay, but more and more non-roleplayers arrived and even worst, some who mocked roleplay (then why were they here?).  The server has some great roleplayers though, and some insane ones (Banegrivm was a roleplayer and totally mad...) but many have left <br>
<br>
One thing though, even if we don't all roleplay, FV has the best rules and the best people in Everquest.<br>
